<item>
            <title>[JDK-8317350] Move code cache purging out of CodeCache::UnloadingScope</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8317350</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Currently, in the destructor of CodeCache::UnloadingScope we flush/purge the code cache from dead nmethods.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This is fairly surprising to do this in the destructor because the purging can take a very signficant amount of time (i.e. 90%+ of total class unloading time).&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Make the flushing/puring explicit.</description>
